We study pulsation timing variations in evolved stars as a method for detecting unseen companions, including exoplanets and low-mass stellar objects. This technique leverages precise timing of stellar oscillations to infer orbital perturbations.

Key goals:
- Model pulsation phase stability
- Constrain companion masses
- Compare with radial velocity methods

This project combines observational data with theoretical modeling of stellar interiors.
